    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-05-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-05-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="200" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d200">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 593.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-05-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 18, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> * * * * * * * *</p>
                <p>You will have received before the arrival of this despatch the answer
                            which I have made to Earl Russell on the subject of the complaint which
                            he preferred against you in relation to your letter to Admiral
                            DuPont.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
